"""
finance_climate_var.py
======================
Monte Carlo Climate Value-at-Risk (CVaR) Engine
Facility: KWB Belchatow lignite mine  |  Issuer: PGE Polska Grupa Energetyczna

Class hierarchy
---------------
BaseUncertaintyLayer          Abstract base — defines the sampling contract.
    EmissionSamplingLayer     Layer 1: Annual emission sampling (truncated normal).
    WindBiasLayer             Layer 2: ERA5 systematic wind bias (normal).
    SpatialExtentLayer        Layer 3: Plume mask / spatial extent jitter (uniform).
    CarbonPriceLayer          Layer 5: Carbon price (log-normal GBM, Amundi 2024).
    RegulatoryPassThroughLayer Layer 6: Regulatory enforcement pass-through (Beta).

ClimateVarEngine              Top-level orchestrator.  Instantiates layers, runs
                              10,000-path Monte Carlo, computes risk metrics, prints
                              the summary table, and saves JSON output.

Usage
-----
    cd methane-api
    python scripts/finance/finance_climate_var.py

Output
------
    scripts/results_analysis/finance_climate_var.json

References
----------
Desnos, Le Guenedal, Morais & Roncalli (Amundi, 2024):
    "From Climate Stress Testing to Climate Value-at-Risk: A Stochastic Approach"
Worden et al. (NIST IR 8575, May 2025):
    "Common Practices for Quantifying Methane Emissions from Plumes
     Detected by Remote Sensing"
"""

